track_notes: It is a long walk for a 2 pointer! In summer this could be very hot; the place to be is the Chapelle St Michel on the crest; on summit you will have plenty room for antennas and have to share with some other Professional antenna! There is plenty room for parking the car. If the sky is clear you will see a nice panorama to the Alpes
track_title: Not the shortest track but the easiest

track_notes: If you follow this track, there is a wide car-park at the end of the small road. as there is plenty path, you must have a card or gps to go on the good ways. The summit is very wide and the panorama is wonderfull to the Alpes and Corsica island.

Starting from the village next to the HEPAD, plenty room for park, you will walk up following the yellow paint, it is a bit difficult some part are very sloop(an sleepy if wet), the summit is large and flat with radio relai and a little shelter; it can be crowded on sundays.
From Levens village. in summer get some water
Nice summit, easy parking car and lot of room for antenna
Not in summertime when temperature are hot
